{"name": "structured-templates", "metadata": {"name": "structured-templates", "version": "0.1.1", "classifiers": [], "home_page": null, "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Templating engine for structured data (no free-form text generation).", "upload_time": 1727173623}, "documentation": ["# structured-templates\n\nThis package implements a simple templating engine for structured data, such as YAML or JSON. It is designed to be\nused in conjunction with any structured data format, such as JSON, YAML or TOML. It provides control elements and\nvariable substition, all based on evaluating keys and strings.\n\n## Example\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: v1\nkind: Secret\ndata:\n  password: ${{ b64encode(secrets.password) }}\n  if(secrets.username):\n    username: ${{ b64encode(secrets.username) }}\n  for(key, value in secrets.additional.items()):\n    ${{ key }}: ${{ b64encode(value) }}\n```\n\nThis example demonstrates how to use the templating engine to generate a Kubernetes Secret object. The `if(...)` and\n`for(...)` control elements are used to conditionally include keys and loop over a dictionary, respectively. The\n`${{ ... }}` syntax is used to evaluate expressions and substitute the result into the template.\n\n## Usage\n\nInstall the package from PyPI:\n\n```bash\npip install structured-templates\n```\n\nThe `TemplateEngine` is the main class that is used to evaluate templates.\n\n```py\nfrom structured_templates import TemplateEngine\n\nengine = TemplateEngine()\nassert engine.evaluate({\"key\": \"${{ 1 + 1 }}\"}) == {\"key\": 2}\n```\n\n## Specification\n\n### Value substitution\n\nValue substitution is done by evaluating an expression and substituting the result into the template. The expression\ncan be any valid Python expression, and the result type is inserted as-is into the template. If the result is a string,\nthe value substition can be prefixed and/or suffixed with text.\n\n```yaml\nkey: prefix${{ expression }}suffix\n10integers: ${{ list(range(10)) }}\n```\n\nAttempting to substitute a non-string value into a string will raise an error.\n\n### Control elements\n\n#### `if(<expr>)`\n\nConditionally include keys in the parent object or items in a list. The value of this control block can only be\na scalar value if the parent object is a list.\n\n> ```yaml\n> items:\n>  - item1\n>  - if(condition): item2\n>  - if(condition):\n>    - item3\n>    - item4\n> ```\n\nMay result in\n\n```yaml\nitems:\n  - item1\n  - item2\n  - item3\n  - item4\n```\n\n#### `for(<names> in <expr>)`\n\nIterate over the elements of an iterable. The value for this field is evaluated in the new scope. If the value is\nan object, the results of every loop are merged into a single object. If the value is a list, the results are\nconcatenated. The value of this control block cannot be a scalar value.\n\n> ```yaml\n> items:\n>   for(idx in range(2)):\n>     ${{ str(idx) }}: Number ${idx}\n> ```\n\nResults in\n\n```yaml\nitems:\n  '0': Number 0\n  '1': Number 1    \n```\n\n#### `macro(<expr>)`\n\nDefine a macro that can be used in the template.\n\n> ```yaml\n> macro(inc(x)): ${{ x + 1 }}\n> key: ${{ inc(1) }}\n> ```\n\nResults in\n\n```yaml\nkey: 2\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "structured_templates.context", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "structured_templates.context.Context", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "structured_templates.context.Context.__post_init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "structured_templates.context.Context.error", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "message", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "TemplateError", "xref": {"fqname": "structured_templates.exceptions.TemplateError", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Create a template error for the context."]}, {"name": "structured_templates.context.Context.format_location", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Format the context location for human readability."]}, {"name": "structured_templates.context.Context.full_scope", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "globals_", "type": {"name": "dict[str, Any] | None", "xref": null, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "ChainMap", "xref": {"fqname": "collections.ChainMap", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Create a ChainMap of the scope."]}], "class_variables": [{"name": "structured_templates.context.Context.parent", "type": {"name": "Context | None", "xref": null, "params": null}, "documentation": ["The parent context. "]}, {"name": "structured_templates.context.Context.key", "type": {"name": "str | int | None", "xref": null, "params": null}, "documentation": ["The name of the key in the parent context that this context was retrieved from. Must be set if [parent] is. "]}, {"name": "structured_templates.context.Context.data", "type": {"name": "T_Value", "xref": {"fqname": "structured_templates.types.T_Value", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["The data of the context. "]}, {"name": "structured_templates.context.Context.scope", "type": {"name": "dict[str, Any] | None", "xref": null, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Variables that are available to expressions in this context. "]}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["A context object holds a value for processing in the template with additional contextual information, such\nas the parent context and key from which the value was retrieved."]}], "exports": []}, {"name": "structured_templates.exceptions", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "structured_templates.exceptions.TemplateError", "bases": ["Exception"], "methods": [{"name": "structured_templates.exceptions.TemplateError.__str__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [{"name": "structured_templates.exceptions.TemplateError.ctx", "type": {"name": "Context", "xref": {"fqname": "structured_templates.context.Context", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "structured_templates.exceptions.TemplateError.message", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Raised for errors during template evaluation."]}], "exports": []}, {"name": "structured_templates", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "structured_templates.TemplateEngine", "xref": {"fqname": "structured_templates.engine.TemplateEngine", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "structured_templates.engine_test", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "structured_templates.engine_test.test_dict_if_condition", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "structured_templates.engine_test.test_dict_for_block", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "structured_templates.engine_test.test_basic_expression", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "return